  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Cameroon  - Flash Floods in Santchou</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contribute to improving the living conditions of 221 most vulnerable families, following the flash floods in Santchou district (West Cameroon).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Since 04 August 2017, the Menoua Division, in the West Region of Cameroon, has been experiencing heavy rainfalls, causing a significant rise of water levels and mudslides to settlements. Resulting from this situation, severe flooding has ensued in the area, causing extensive material damage and loss of life.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The needs of the most vulnerable families will be met through distribution of food and non food items, promotion of hygiene and sanitation, mobilizing volunteers, production of educational materials on water, sanitation, and hygiene, and a continued assessment of community needs.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project takes place in Santchou district (West Cameroon).</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will reach 221 vulnerable families.</narrative>
  </description>
